3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour based on the 8-hour TWAP of the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The on-chain settlement occurs automatically through smart contracts with sub-second finality on Hyperliquid's L1. Funding payments are exchanged directly between long and short position holders without counterparty risk, with rates typically ranging from -0.1% to 0.3% per hour during volatile periods."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SHIB","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SHIB/USDT generates substantial funding rate opportunities due to frequent retail FOMO cycles and high leverage usage among meme coin traders. The pair's large trading volume on Hyperliquid provides sufficient liquidity for meaningful arbitrage positions while the 1-hour funding frequency allows for more responsive rate adjustments compared to 8-hour intervals on CEXs."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SHIB funding rates on Hyperliquid typically spike during social media-driven rallies, often exceeding 0.5% per hour when retail traders pile into leveraged longs. Negative rates frequently occur during broader market downturns when short interest dominates. The 1-hour intervals create more granular rate adjustments compared to traditional exchanges, resulting in 8-24 funding payments per day. Weekend periods often show reduced volatility in funding rates due to lower trading activity, while major Shiba Inu ecosystem announcements can trigger sustained positive funding rate periods lasting 12-24 hours."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage between Hyperliquid and CEXs like Binance or OKX becomes profitable when funding rate differentials exceed transaction costs and slippage. The on-chain nature allows for automated arbitrage strategies through smart contracts, eliminating manual execution delays. Delta-neutral positions can capture funding payments while maintaining market exposure neutrality through simultaneous long/short positions across venues. High-frequency arbitrageurs benefit from Hyperliquid's sub-second settlement times and the ability to react quickly to funding rate divergences during volatile SHIB price movements."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid's single L1 architecture creates concentration risk, though the platform's on-chain transparency provides real-time position and liquidation visibility. USDC-only settlements require stablecoin exposure rather than USDT, potentially affecting arbitrage calculations during depeg events. The newer platform lacks the extensive track record of established CEXs, making position sizing crucial for risk management. Meme coin volatility can trigger rapid liquidations, and the 1-hour funding frequency, while advantageous for arbitrage, requires constant monitoring to avoid unexpected funding cost accumulation during extended positions."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are SHIB funding rates updated on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding rates are calculated and paid every hour on Hyperliquid, providing 24 funding payments per day. This higher frequency compared to 8-hour intervals on most CEXs allows for more responsive rate adjustments during SHIB volatility spikes."},{"question":"Can I automate SHIB funding rate arbitrage on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Yes, Hyperliquid's on-chain infrastructure supports automated trading through smart contracts and APIs. You can build delta-neutral strategies that automatically capture funding rate differentials while managing position sizes based on predefined risk parameters."},{"question":"What makes SHIB funding rates different on Hyperliquid vs CEXs?","answer":"Hyperliquid's 1-hour funding intervals and on-chain settlement create more granular rate adjustments and eliminate counterparty risk. The DEX structure also means funding rates reflect pure supply/demand dynamics without exchange intervention, often leading to more extreme rates during meme coin rallies."},{"question":"What are the typical funding rate ranges for SHIB on Hyperliquid?","answer":"SHIB funding rates typically range from -0.2% to 0.4% per hour during normal conditions, but can exceed 0.8% hourly during major rallies or social media events. Negative rates below -0.3% are common during broader crypto market corrections when short interest dominates."}]}]
